00:22:24.960 --> 00:22:31.380
Now, let’s go on to this video’s quiz.
Select the best answer from the available

00:22:31.380 --> 00:22:37.619
choices. In some cases there are multiple
answers that could possibly be correct, but

00:22:37.619 --> 00:22:43.379
there will always be one best choice. Cisco
exams tend to have lots of questions like

00:22:43.379 --> 00:22:49.470
that, so hopefully some of these will be able
to test you in a similar manner. This first

00:22:49.470 --> 00:22:55.379
video’s quiz questions, however, shouldn’t
be too difficult.

00:22:55.379 --> 00:22:59.259
Your company wants to purchase some network
hardware to which they can connect the 30

00:22:59.259 --> 00:23:10.159
PCs in your department. Which type of network
device is appropriate? A, a router. B, a firewall.

00:23:10.159 --> 00:23:24.159
C, a switch. Or D, a server. Pause the video
to think about your answer. The answer is

00:23:24.159 --> 00:23:31.739
C, a switch. Let’s analyze each of the incorrect
answers first, then the correct answer.

00:23:31.739 --> 00:23:39.899
A router, like this Cisco ISR 900 series router,
is designed for forwarding traffic between

00:23:39.899 --> 00:23:45.609
networks, not for connecting lots of end hosts
like PCs to.

00:23:45.609 --> 00:23:49.720
Also, a router will not typically have 30 network
interfaces to connect hosts to.

00:23:49.720 --> 00:23:55.080
So, A, a router, is incorrect.

00:23:55.080 --> 00:24:01.919
A firewall, like this Cisco ASA 5500-X series
firewall, is designed to filter traffic as

00:24:01.919 --> 00:24:07.739
it enters and exits the local network. It
is not designed to connect directly to end

00:24:07.739 --> 00:24:12.429
hosts, and typically will not have enough
network interfaces for 30 hosts.

00:24:12.429 --> 00:24:18.440
So, B, a firewall, is incorrect.

00:24:18.440 --> 00:24:24.110
A server is an end host itself, not a networking
device to which you will connect other end

00:24:24.110 --> 00:24:30.519
hosts.
So, D, a server, is incorrect.

00:24:30.519 --> 00:24:37.409
A switch, like this Cisco Catalyst 9200 series
switch, is designed to connect many end hosts

00:24:37.409 --> 00:24:43.220
in the same LAN together. They include many
network interfaces to connect hosts to.

00:24:43.220 --> 00:24:52.600
So, C, a switch, is the correct answer. Okay
let’s go on to the next question.

00:24:52.600 --> 00:24:58.889
You received a video file from your friend’s
Apple iPhone using AirDrop. What was his iPhone

00:24:58.889 --> 00:25:10.560
functioning as in that transaction? A, a server.
B, a client. Or C, a local area network. Pause

00:25:10.560 --> 00:25:17.640
the video to think about your answer.

00:25:17.640 --> 00:25:24.560
The answer is A, a server. Lets’ check the answers.

00:25:24.560 --> 00:25:30.490
In this case your iPhone, not your friend’s
iPhone.

00:25:30.490 --> 00:25:34.419
A client accesses a service, it does not provide
a service.

00:25:34.419 --> 00:25:40.120
So, B, a client, is incorrect.

00:25:40.120 --> 00:25:46.809
An end host like an iPhone does not function
as a local area network (LAN) by itself. It

00:25:46.809 --> 00:25:56.899
can, however, be a part of a local area network.
So, C, a local area network, is incorrect.

00:25:56.899 --> 00:26:01.559
A server is a device that provides functions
or services for clients.

00:26:01.559 --> 00:26:05.809
In this case, your friend’s phone provided
the file to your iPhone.

00:26:05.809 --> 00:26:14.460
So, A, a server, is the correct answer. Let’s
go to the next question.

00:26:14.460 --> 00:26:21.580
What is your computer or smartphone functioning
as while you watch this video? A, a server.

00:26:21.580 --> 00:26:34.559
B, an end host. Or C, a client. Pause the
video to think about your answer. The answer

00:26:34.559 --> 00:26:40.399
is C, a client. Let’s check the answers.

00:26:40.399 --> 00:26:46.549
Your device is receiving a service, not providing
one, so it is not functioning as a server.

00:26:46.549 --> 00:26:52.230
Therefore A, a server, is incorrect.

00:26:52.230 --> 00:26:57.999
Although your device is an end host, that
does not describe its function. Both servers

00:26:57.999 --> 00:27:06.889
and clients are end hosts in a network.
So, B, an end host, is incorrect.

00:27:06.889 --> 00:27:12.519
Your device is receiving a service from YouTube’s
servers. Therefore, it is functioning as a

00:27:12.519 --> 00:27:16.899
client.
So, C, a client, is the correct answer. Let’s

00:27:16.899 --> 00:27:20.409
go to the next question.

00:27:20.409 --> 00:27:24.679
Your company wants to purchase some network
hardware to connect its separate networks

00:27:24.680 --> 00:27:38.649
together. What kind of network device is appropriate?
A, a firewall. B, a host. C, a LAN. Or D,

00:27:38.649 --> 00:27:46.880
a router. Pause the video to think about your
answer.

00:27:46.880 --> 00:27:52.440
The answer is D, a router. Let's check.

00:27:52.540 --> 00:27:58.039
Although a firewall can connect multiple networks
together, its real purpose is to monitor and

00:27:58.039 --> 00:28:01.119
control traffic as it enters and exits the
network.

00:28:01.119 --> 00:28:07.519
So, A, a firewall, is not the best answer.

00:28:07.519 --> 00:28:16.380
The term ‘host’ can refer to any type
of network node. So B, a host, is incorrect.

00:28:16.380 --> 00:28:24.779
LAN stands for Local Area Network. A LAN is
not a network device itself. So, C, a LAN,

00:28:24.779 --> 00:28:26.259
is incorrect.

00:28:26.259 --> 00:28:31.330
A router is a device that is designed to connect
and forward network traffic between multiple

00:28:31.330 --> 00:28:38.840
networks. So, D, a router, is the correct
answer. Let’s go to the final quiz question

00:28:38.840 --> 00:28:41.889
for this video.

00:28:41.889 --> 00:28:46.210
Your company wants to upgrade its old network
firewall that has been in use for several

00:28:46.210 --> 00:28:52.989
years to one that provides more advanced functions.
What kind of firewall should they purchase?

00:28:52.989 --> 00:29:05.619
A, a host-based firewall. B, a next-level
firewall. C, a next-generation firewall. Or

00:29:05.620 --> 00:29:15.160
D, a top-layer firewall. Pause the video to
think about your answer.

00:29:15.320 --> 00:29:23.480
The answer is C, a next-generation firewall. Let’s check
each answer.

00:29:23.489 --> 00:29:28.679
A host-based firewall is a piece of software
that runs on an end host, like the firewall

00:29:28.679 --> 00:29:38.940
on your computer. It is not a network firewall.
So A, a host-based firewall, is incorrect.

00:29:38.940 --> 00:29:45.519
Next-level and Top-layer are not actual types
of firewalls, so B and D are incorrect.

00:29:45.519 --> 00:29:52.989
A next-generation firewall combines traditional
firewall features with more advanced filtering

00:29:52.989 --> 00:29:58.570
functionalities. So C, a next-generation firewall,
is correct.

